1. Game mechanics - Describes how gameplay functions and interacts.  
2. Graphics quality - Evaluates visual appeal and realism of the game.  
3. User interface - Assesses ease of navigation and accessibility.  
4. Sound design - Analyzes audio elements and immersion in the game.  
5. Replay value - Considers likelihood of playing again after completion.  
6. Difficulty level - Rates challenge and skill required to progress.  
7. Storyline depth - Measures complexity and engagement of the narrative.  
8. Character development - Evaluates growth and relatability of characters.  
9. Technical performance - Examines stability, bugs, and loading times.  
10. Compatibility - Assesses support for different devices or systems.
